/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7574:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:9:This chain has real upside. If a genuinely exact small helical/Fourier subsystem existed that stayed phase-locked long enough to realize Tao-like delayed transfer under honest conjugate and spectator accounting, the firewall would indeed be in serious trouble quickly.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7575:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:23:- "Smallest honest support family" is undefined. Smallest by mode count, shell count, active triads, parameter dimension, or closure depth? Without a strict ordering, Step 1 can be gamed indefinitely.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7576:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:24:- The chain confuses decisive positive evidence with informative negative evidence. A positive exact construction would kill the firewall. A negative search over a handcrafted family does not support the firewall much unless the search space is proved exhaustive.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7577:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:25:- It pushes honesty checks too late. Spectator channels, closure cascades, and robustness are treated as downstream tests, but they should constrain the candidate family from the start.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7578:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:28:- Its kill conditions are mostly qualitative. Phrases like "meaningful phase-locking ansatz," "ordinary cascade behavior," and "meaningful delayed transfer event" are too elastic for a search procedure that is already parameter-rich.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7579:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:32:### Step 1 - Freeze the smallest honest support family
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7580:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:36:- The step mixes "mode family" and "packet family" language. Those are not interchangeable. If this is really an exact finite-dimensional invariant subsystem search, packet talk is already suspicious because packet localization is not itself an exact invariant notion.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7581:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:51:- This step is where the chain turns from analysis into parameter fishing. Once geometry, helicity, amplitudes, and scale ratio are all free, "search for a usable delayed window" can absorb a lot of failed structure behind tuning.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7582:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:57:### Step 4 - Test stability of the locking window against spectators and viscosity
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7583:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:59:- Spectators are being treated too late. If they matter enough to kill the window, they matter enough to belong in the exact support audit from Step 1 onward. Deferring them to Step 4 makes the earlier subsystem look cleaner than it really is.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7584:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:60:- "Measure how long the phase-locking manifold or near-manifold persists" sounds numerical and trajectory-specific. That is weak evidence unless the chain states a robustness standard: open set of initial data, codimension-one tuning, or exact invariant family.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7585:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:62:- The step asks whether spectator channels stay subordinate during the window, but does not define a subordinate threshold. If the firewall is about delayed transfer surviving honest spectator burden, that threshold should have been explicit much earlier.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7586:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:69:- A negative outcome is much less informative than the step implies. If the chosen subsystem fails because of coefficient rigidity or spectator blowup, that may be a defect of the chosen minimal family, not a firewall-level obstruction.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall-step-001-explorer-001.log:7587:missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:70:- The handoff menu is too coarse. "Coefficient rigidity" or "no honest delayed window" is not yet reusable unless the chain has proved that the obstruction survives changes of support size, geometry class, or role assignment.
